<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07874</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE SCHOOL HEALTH AND SAFETY OFFICE IN EVERY PUBLIC SCHOOL IN THE COUNTRY, PROVIDING FUNDS THEREFOR, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Establishes the  School Health and Safety Office (SHSO) which shall be primarily responsible for the supervision and operation of the school canteen, school nutrition program, immunization campaigns, campus security, and many other related non-teaching roles and functions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “School Health and Safety Act of 2018.” </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ABAYON, HARLIN NEIL III J.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-06-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-08-07)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2018-07-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION</td></tr></table>